<main class="container">
  <h2>Agile Model</h2>
  <p>
    Agile is an iterative approach to software development that focuses on
    flexibility, collaboration, and continuous improvement.
  </p>

  <section class="card">
    <h3>Key Ideas</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Short development cycles called sprints</li>
      <li>Frequent feedback from users</li>
      <li>Team collaboration</li>
      <li>Quick adaptation to change</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="card">
    <h3>Advantages</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Flexible requirements</li>
      <li>Fast delivery of small updates</li>
      <li>Strong communication with stakeholders</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="card">
    <h3>Challenges</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Requires active collaboration</li>
      <li>Can be difficult without clear planning</li>
      <li>Scope can change often</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</main>

